comments: I took this professor two semester ago..really hate the guy is leaving..By far one of the best professors I have had at the u of m..almost like a high school teacher more than a professor by the way he cares

Why is Jeremy leaving the U of M???? The Spanish dept needs him! i had to take 1020 twice because the two profs i took before him couldnt explain the material. i get to 2010 and this guy explains everything with crystal clarity. wtf, uofm?! plus he\'s engaging, makes you think (a little too hard sometimes), and he\'s the funniest person ever

Professor Crowe kept the class entertaining w/his comments, stories and funny jokes he made Spanish fun and easier to learn, sad he is leaving. I honestly learned a lot in just a short period of time!!!
Mr. Crowe is terrific. Funny, interesting, smart, good teacher. Good class. Lot of fun.

Mr. Crowe is a really good teacher. He gave us a lot of opportunities to improve our grades. He understands if you have personal stuff and he cares that you are learning the material. I think I learned more how to be a student in his class than I have my other classes. He\'s also really funny and had us rollin all semester.

He is absolutely terrible! I study, study, study, but somehow he still finds the most random and obscure questions for the tests. Furthermore, many of the students that repeatedly don\'t study or do anything somehow have earned higher grades than me and other who HAVE studied their butts off!!
This guy is awful!

This teacher is AWESOME!He is very caring and helpful. He doesn\'t mind calling you out if you are talking during the lecture or not participated. Overall he has a great teaching method, he is so super patient and the learning enviroment is laid back. Professor Crowe is great. Take Him :-).
very good teacher had him for 1010 and 1020, interested in students learning and very laid back and fun. will take all 4 spanish from him, also very helpful...

An amazing teacher. Would give you the shirt off his back if you needed it. Cares about your progress, gives you lots of opportunities. Always available. I wish he was teaching 2010 because I\'d take him.

He speaks in Spanish too much and is too fast when he does. He expects you to memorize the syllabus. His tests are really hard. I had him last semester for 1010 and he wasn\'t this hard. I don\'t know what happened but this semester he is really demanding and expects a lot.

professor crowe is 2 funny!!!!!1! and he will call you out so fast! but he\'s really good at explaning stuf and i think he really cares about his students. i know he\'s always available to talk or explain something to him. will make you laugh and you will learn.
J.C. IS FUNNY. KIND OF A LITTLE SARCASTIC, BUT A EASY CLASS. TAKE HIM.. YOU WOULD HAVE A GREAT TIME AND HE IS A GREAT TEACHER!!!!!!
Great teacher! He is hilarious! Cares about student\'s success. Would take Spanish from him over and over again. Favorite teacher yet.

He is the most organized person I\'ve ever met. Mr. Crowe is constantly on his game, gives good examples, and makes sure you get your every penny\'s worth of the textbook. I think he\'s sometimes too demanding and there\'s a lot of writing, but he\'s the greatest language teacher I\'ve had in four years. I\'ve never laughed as hard or learned as much.

This guy will keep you on your toes! Mr Crowe is super funny and super cool and really cares that people are learning. He totally calls you out and will get an attitude with you if you cop one with him. He\'s understanding and NOT UNREASONABLE! I learned more in this one class that I have in the past three semesters. LOT OF WRITING HERE THOUGH.

He\'s my favorite professor so far in college. I think he might be gay, but I\'m not sure. It\'s so hard to tell these days. But he\'s really funny. And he gives you a lot of opportunities other teachers wouldn\'t. I know that if you make a C or lower and a test, he\'ll make you come to his office, but he\'s real understanding. I like him a lot.

Mr. Crowe is not unreasonable (and he\'ll tell you - believe me). His class is really fun, but unlike some of the TAs I\'ve had before, he actually cares and takes his job seriously. And he\'s really, really good at it. I am taking him for 1020. He really is an amazing teacher.
he\'s a great guy and really, really funny. you better come to class or he\'ll call you out on it. he\'s really helpful. i\'m going to take him for 1020.
One of the best teachers I have ever had. Period.
